<paragraph blockId="24.[150,1437,152,2034]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1435,152,255]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,364,1698,1724]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Observations</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leme" authorityYear="2011" box="[402,629,1699,1724]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Vriesea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minutiflora">
<emphasis box="[402,629,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Vriesea minutiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of section 
<taxonomicName authority="(E. Morren) Wawra ex Wittm." authorityName="Wittm." baseAuthorityName="E. Morren" box="[909,1359,1698,1724]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Xiphion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[909,1002,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Xiphion</emphasis>
(E.Morren) Wawra ex Wittm.
</taxonomicName>
, being most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Leme (1993: 2)" authorityName="Leme" authorityPageNumber="2" authorityYear="1993" box="[334,792,1737,1763]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Vriesea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="ruschii" subSpecies="leonii">
<emphasis box="[334,444,1737,1762]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">V. ruschii</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[533,600,1737,1762]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">leonii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Leme, E. M. C." box="[607,792,1737,1763]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref22272" refString="Leme, E. M. C. (1993) Novas Bromeliaceas Nativas do Brasil - IX. Pabstia 4 (1): 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1993">Leme (1993: 2)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which is a taxon currently under study to reevaluate it and elevate its status to species rank (Leme unpubl.). The morphological differences to be highlighted in comparison with the latter are: the arcuate leaves (vs. suberect), comparatively longer inflorescence (
<quantity metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="45.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="30.0">30–60 cm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity box="[240,361,1853,1879]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="27.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="20.0">20–35 cm</quantity>
long), bearing lateral branches with more numerous flowers (11–23 vs. 8–15 flowers), stramineous floral bracts (vs. pale green) with the basal ones carinate (vs. ecarinate) and smaller (12–16 × 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10– 13 mm</quantity>
vs. ca. 20 × 
<quantity box="[382,469,1930,1956]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="18.0">18 mm</quantity>
), smaller flowers (26–27 vs. 
<quantity box="[809,891,1930,1956]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="35.0">35 mm</quantity>
long), smaller sepals (16–17 × 
<quantity box="[1262,1355,1930,1956]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8-9 mm</quantity>
vs. ca. 20 × 
<quantity box="[212,300,1969,1995]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
), and also by the smaller petals (20–23 × 
<quantity box="[793,905,1969,1995]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="10.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="9.0">9–12 mm</quantity>
vs. ca. 28 × 
<quantity box="[1058,1145,1969,1995]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
). On the other hand, this new species can be associated to 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith (1960: 255)" authorityName="Smith" authorityPageNumber="255" authorityYear="1960" box="[549,913,2008,2034]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Vriesea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cearensis">
<emphasis box="[549,691,2008,2033]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">V. cearensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, L. B." box="[699,913,2008,2034]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="249 - 257" refId="ref23572" refString="Smith, L. B. (1960) Notes on Bromeliaceae XV. Phytologia. 7 (5): 249 - 257." type="journal article" year="1960">Smith (1960:255)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, differing by the acuminate peduncle bracts (vs. rounded and minutely apiculate), longer inflorescence (30–60 vs. 
<quantity box="[1010,1130,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="22.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="20.0">20–25 cm</quantity>
long) with longer lateral branches (14–22 vs. 
<quantity box="[398,501,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="11.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="9.0">9–13 cm</quantity>
long) and more numerous flowers per branch (11–23 vs. 4–9 flowers), and by the larger petals appendages (8–11 × 
<quantity box="[587,705,229,255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2–2.5 mm</quantity>
vs. 6 × 
<quantity box="[799,894,229,255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
